results.title: Introduction
results.description: Welcome to this Node.js course! Let me introduce myself and give you a rough overview of this course and what it's all about!

results.title: What is Node.js?
results.description: What is Node.js? That's the most important question in a Node course I'd argue and in this lecture, we'll explore what exactly NodeJS is and why it's amazing.

results.title: Installing Node.js and Creating our First App
Join our Online Learning Community
results.description: Learning alone is absolutely fine but finding learning partners might be a nice thing, too. Our learning community is a great place to learn and grow together - of course it's 100% free and optional!

results.title: Installing Node.js and Creating our First App
results.description: We know what NodeJS is about - let's now see it in action. For that, let's install Node.js and create our first little application in this lecture.

results.title: Understanding the Role & Usage of Node.js
results.description: Node.js can be used for a broad variety of things - web servers being the most prominent use-case probably. In this lecture, you'll get an overview of the different things NodeJS can be used for.

results.title: Course Outline
results.description: We got a good idea of what Node.js is, now it's time to understand what exactly is in the course. In this lecture, I'll give you a good overview of the course content and the order in which it is presented.

results.title: How To Get The Most Out Of The Course
results.description: Your course success matters to me, hence in this lecture, I'll share some best practices regarding the course taking process and how you can get the most out of this course.

results.title: Working with the REPL vs Using FIles
Working with the REPL vs Using Files
results.description: When writing Node code, you got two main options: Files which you execute or the REPL. This lecture explains + explores both alternatives.

results.title: Using the Attached Source Code
results.description: Stuck? Got an error you can't debug on your own? You find snapshots of my code attached to multiple lectures in the course! More information can be found in this lecture.
